The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Q amp;A

 Little wonder

 My minor daughter takes part in various cultural shows and gets paid for her performance. Should I club her income with mine and pay income tax on that?

 Ritesh Arora, Calcutta

 come of a minor child arising from any activity involving application of skill, talent or specialised knowledge is assessed in the hands of the minor child and not clubbed with the parents income.

 Overseas call

 I am leaving India and going to relocate in Canada. What are the formalities I require to complete regarding my financial affairs in India?

 Kingshuk Basu, by e-mail 

 You will have to inform the income-tax authorities about the change in your residential status. You will also have to communicate to your banker that the local bank accounts have to be now treated as NRI accounts so that the bank redesignates them as NRO accounts. Also, if you hold any shares or debentures, you will have to inform the companies concerned about the change in your status as NRI. You are eligible to repatriate income earned in India from rupee assets held in the country.

 Looking for ELSS

 Kindly mention some mutual fund ELSS schemes where we can invest money for tax exemption under section 80C.

 Subhas De, Hooghly

 Most of the mutual fund houses have such schemes. However, as with all mutual fund schemes, one should invest based on various parameters. You can contact a mutual fund distributor or agent. Generally, the names of these schemes have the phrase tax saving or similar terms.

 Learning exercise

 Can I claim exemption for repayment of education loan over and above exemption for tuition fees paid?

 G. Bhattacharya, Midnapur

 Exemption for payment of tuition fees is available to parents paying for up to two children under section 80C up to Rs 1 lakh. On the contrary, exemption for repayment of education loan is available to an individual taking such a loan and not to parents who avail of it for their children.

